      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a crucial legal concept that protects fundamental rights, ensuring the government cannot infringe upon deeply held liberties even if it follows proper procedures. It acts as a bulwark against government overreach, safeguarding personal autonomy against legislative intrusion. This doctrine has historically been vital in expanding civil rights, protecting freedoms that the Constitution doesn't explicitly list but which are inherent to liberty.",
      "source": "target",
