      "content": "A strong conclusion should emphasize that the protection of fundamental, inherent rights is the bedrock of a truly just society, regardless of legal debates. While critics focus on judicial overreach, the very concept of substantive due process reflects a necessary commitment to human dignity over rigid legal formalism. Therefore, the enduring importance of these protections outweighs the theoretical risks of judicial interpretation.",
      "source": "target",
